1 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana does hereby
2 establish and provide for the Task Force on Gestational Carrier Agreements and Assisted
3 Reproductive Regulation to study the implementation and regulation of gestational carrier
4 agreements in this state, and may propose recommendations, together with specific
5 proposals, for legislation. Any recommendations or proposals shall be submitted by written
6 report to the legislature and to the David R. Poynter Legislative Research Library as required
7 by R.S. 24:771 and 772.
8 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the legislature recommends that the task force
9 include consideration of all of the following:
10 (1) Whether and how this state should recognize and regulate gestational carrier
11 agreements.
12 (2) Development of a regulatory framework consistent with the Human Embryo
13 Statutes, R.S. 9:121 through 133.
14 (3) Compliance with applicable federal nondiscrimination and privacy laws,
15 including the Affordable Care Act, the Americans with Disabilities Act, and the Health
16 Insurance Portability and Accountability Act.
17 (4) Appropriate regulatory authority and oversight responsibilities among the
18 Louisiana Department of Health, the courts, the Department of Justice, and other state
19 agencies.
20 (5) Financial eligibility standards, escrow requirements, compensation protections,
21 and related safeguards for gestational carriers that protect participants without creating
22 discriminatory barriers.
23 (6) Standards governing informed consent and medical decision-making authority
24 during assisted reproductive and gestational carrier arrangements.
25 (7) Development of data collection, reporting, and record retention standards relating
26 to gestational carrier arrangements and assisted reproductive practices.
27 (8) Ethical considerations relating to reproductive medicine, family formation, and
28 maternal and child health.
